st/SKILL.md:87:   - Expected minimum: metadata validation, compile, JVM tests, native-image compile, and native-image runtime tests are green for the target coordinate.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:99:- No legacy native-image metadata config files are introduced.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:108:- The PR fixes native behavior by skipping, disabling, swallowing, or weakening the failing path.\n./skills/review-library-update-request/SKILL.md:186:- Bad native-image skip:\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Native-image execution should remain enabled by default when the repaired test reaches the native lane. Do not accept changes that skip or short-circuit native-image behavior. When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally relies on open-ended dynamic class loading that native image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, accept the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`. Reject raw native-only skips, bare `catch (Error)` blocks, and use of this pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:23:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:46:   - Reject or request changes if the PR removes tests, disables test classes, catches and ignores the failing exception, or disables native-image behavior.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:77:   - Prefer seeing the full target `test` lane green because a Java runtime fix can still reduce native-image coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:78:   - If current-defaults and future-defaults lanes both run, both should pass unless the PR clearly targets only one failing lane and the other failure is unrelated infrastructure noise.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:93:- The fix makes JVM tests pass by deleting tests, skipping execution, swallowing the failing exception.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:94:- The fix disables native-image behavior instead of using the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern for unsupported open-ended dynamic class loading.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:113:- For swallowed exceptions: say that catching or ignoring the failing exception hides the runtime failure instead of proving the library behavior works.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:114:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:138:- Bad native-image skip:\n./skills/README.md:42:### `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`\n./skills/README.md:44:Reviews pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label.\n./skills/README.md:45:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:52:### `close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs`\n./skills/README.md:54:Closes batches of open pull requests that have the `human-intervention` label or failing CI.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:27: * Gradle task to fix test failures during native-image runs.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:33: *  -PnewLibraryVersion: New version of the library that is failing\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:59:    @Option(option = \"newLibraryVersion\", description = \"New version of library that is failing\")\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:25:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. New-library metadata must be provided through `reachability-metadata.json`, including any test-only metadata under `tests/src/**`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:97:- For native skips that does not depend on the open-ended dynamic class loading: say that the PR avoids the failing native path instead of fixing it, so it does not demonstrate native-image runtime coverage.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:123:- Native-image skip:\n./COVERAGE.md:414:| `io.github.resilience4j:resilience4j-spring-boot3` | [2.3.0<br>- 2.4.0](metadata/io.github.resilience4j/resilience4j-spring-boot3/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Resilience4j Spring Boot 3 integrates Resilience4j fault-tolerance modules with Spring Boot 3 applications. It provides auto-configuration, configuration properties, Actuator endpoints, health indicators, metrics, and native-image hints for circuit breakers, retries, rate limiters, bulkheads, and time limiters.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/io.github.resilience4j/resilience4j-spring-boot3/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:701:| `org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core` | [7.0.0<br>- 15.0.2](metadata/org.apache.arrow/arrow-memory-core/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Apache Arrow Memory Core provides the core Java off-heap memory management APIs used by Arrow libraries and applications, including allocators, buffers, reference management, and allocation accounting. It is the foundation Arrow Java modules use to allocate and track Arrow buffers consistently across memory implementations.</details> | [94.1% (16/17 calls)](stats/org.apache.arrow/arrow-memory-core/) |\n./COVERAGE.md:1200:| `org.scalacheck:scalacheck_2.13` | [1.18.1<br>- 1.19.0](metadata/org.scalacheck/scalacheck_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> ScalaCheck is a Scala property-based testing library for generating test data and checking properties over many randomized cases. It can be used standalone or with Scala test frameworks to exercise Scala and Java code and shrink failing examples.</details> | [100.0% (12/12 calls)](stats/org.scalacheck/scalacheck_2.13/) |\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:2:name: review-fixes-native-image-run-fail\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:7:# Review `fixes-native-image-run-fail` PRs\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:15:- Confirm the PR has label `fixes-native-image-run-fail`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept fixes that hide the failing native path by skipping assertions, skipping native-image runtime execution, or weakening the test until the failure disappears.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:22:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:29:   - Confirm the PR has label `fixes-native-image-run-fail`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject or request changes if the PR fixes the native run by disabling the failing behavior.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:47:3. Review the native-image fix.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:73:   - Expected minimum: native-image compile and native test execution are green for the target coordinate.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:75:   - If current-defaults and future-defaults lanes both run, both should pass unless the PR clearly targets only one failing lane and the other failure is unrelated infrastructure noise.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:82:- The PR is scoped to the target existing library